  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "CPU WDG will start automatically during Power ON or wakeup. Recovery timer will also start along with CPU watchdog and default Reset for SMU Recovery timer will be Application Reset"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Calculation of WDG Timeout with reload value"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Formula for WDG timeout is."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "WDG Period = ((2^16- Reload Value ) *divider)/ fSPB"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Divider value can be 64, 256, 16384"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "fSPB - System Peripheral Bus clock value"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "For example, If the reload value is 0xFE00 with clock configuration of fSPB as 100 MHz and divider value as 16384"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Calculation%20of%20WDG%20Timeout%20value%20-%20Internal%20WDG/image-2023-9-4_15-43-45.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Calculation of WDG Timeout value - Internal WDG/image-2023-9-4_15-43-45.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The WDG timeout value is"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "WDG timeout = (( 0x10000 - 0xFE00) * 16384)/100 MHz = 8388608/100000000 = 0.08388 seconds = 83ms = ~80 ms"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "WDG default timeout after Reset"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "WDG Period = ((2^16- Reload Value ) *divider)/ fSPB"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "= ((0x10000 - 0xFFFC) * 16384)/50 MHz = 0.0013 seconds = 1.3 ms"
    }
  ],
